This flowchart shows the process of using a loop to display the message “HELLO, FBC” 10 times. The program starts, then checks whether the loop has already run 10 times. If the answer is No, the program outputs or displays “HELLO, FBC” and repeats the process again. The loop continues until the message has been displayed 10 times. Once the loop reaches 10 repetitions, the answer becomes Yes, and the program stops. This flowchart demonstrates the concept of iteration or looping in programming.
